entries.title: How Red Bull's Dietrich Mateschitz turned Thai duck farmer's 'hangover cure' into business empire
entries.description: The Austrian, who became known later in his life for his love of motorsports, extreme sports and football, passed away this week after a battle with illness, the company announced yesterday.

entries.title: Red Bull tycoon Dietrich Mateschitz marketed it as a magic potion, writes CHRISTOPHER STEVENS
entries.description: CHRISTOPHER STEVENS: Red Bull made tycoon Dietrich Mateschitz, who died aged 78, a £22 billion fortune, making him the 51st wealthiest man in the world, according to the Forbes rich list.

entries.title: Diamonds player Donnell Wallam 'devastated' after Gina Rinehart, Netball Australia fallout
entries.description: Diamonds player Donnell Wallam kicked off the saga after asking for an exemption to wearing the Hancock Prospecting logo on the team jersey.

entries.title: Race For PM: Boris Johnson BOWS OUT of Tory leadership race, lining up Rishi Sunak for PM
entries.description: MAILONLINE BLOG: All the news and updates on the race to succeed Liz Truss as Prime Minister on October 23, 2022, as it happened.

entries.title: Netball Australia targeted by cruel trolls after Gina Rinehart fallout
entries.description: The sports organisation has been left searching for a new sponsor after Ms Rinehart's mining company Hancock Prospecting pulled the plug on Saturday.

entries.title: LinkedIn post about female CEO of Travis Schultz and Partners sparks debate
entries.description: Female lawyers have blown up online about what they believe are sexist remarks by a partner in a Brisbane law firm after he posted photos of the company's CEO vacuuming the office.

entries.title: Jeffrey Dahmer's 86-year-old father is pelted with women's underwear
entries.description: Sick fans of serial killer Jeffrey Dahmer have begun targeting the twisted murderer's 86-year-old father Lionel in Ohio with one woman throwing her underwear at him.

entries.title: Federal budget 2023: Anthony Albanese, Jim Chalmers on 'sensible' savings amid high inflation
entries.description: Prime Minister Anthony Albanese and his ministers believe they are ready to launch into the task of budget repair after inheriting a structural deficit and record levels of debt.

entries.title: Three million Britons in global medical study to help develop new ways to detect illnesses sooner
entries.description: It is hoped the research will help doctors better predict who is at higher risk of diseases such as cancer, diabetes, heart disease, dementia and stroke.

entries.title: North and South Korea exchange warning shots along disputed sea boundary
entries.description: North and South Korea say they have exchanged warning shots along their disputed western sea boundary, weeks after tensions over missile tests. (Pictured: North Korean leader Kim Jong-Un)

entries.title: Humpback whale pull off incredible move to free itself from the ropes of a buoy in Canada
entries.description: Fisheries and Oceans Canada managed to come to the mammal's help off Texada Island in British Columbia, as the whale performed a rare move by 'spyhopping' to get trapped fish nets in its mouth.

entries.title: Twitter users react with hilarious social media memes as Johnson pulls out Tory leadership race
entries.description: News that former Prime Minister Boris Johnson has dropped out of the Tory leadership race tonight was met with a flurry of memes of social media.

entries.title: Patients face a 55-day wait for cancer treatment as backlog worsens after Covid pandemic
entries.description: The UK came 33rd out of 41 developed nations for cancer mortality in 2019, the Organisation for Economic Co-operation and Development (OECD) found.

entries.title: German climate activists throw MASH POTATOES over Monet's 'Les Meules' at the Barberini Museum
entries.description: BREAKING NEWS: Activists from the 'Letzte Generation' climate activist group entered the museum before throwing paint on the painting, which sold at auction for $110million in 2019.

entries.title: All That I Forgot: Anne Howell thought she was a little girl after coma and retrograde amnesia
entries.description: Anne Howell was a 30-year-old journalist when she underwent brain surgery, contracted meningitis and fell into a coma. When she woke she was diagnosed with retrograde amnesia.

entries.title: Woman breaks taboo as she admits 'loathing' being a mum - after spending £100,000 to have a baby
entries.description: Alice Mann opens up about how her dream of being a mother has now become a 'nightmare' - after she spent around £100,000 to try and get pregnant. Stock images used.

entries.title: Maryland couple claim STRANGERS have moved into the $379,600 house they just bought
entries.description: A Maryland couple signed a contract with US Bank to purchase the five-bedroom home at 10716 Dragoo Place in Clinton, Maryland on Thursday only to find people moving into the home.

entries.title: Liz Truss parties at Chequers in her final days as PM
entries.description: The departing premier, who resigned this week after a disastrous 44-day spell in No10, is using the grace-and-favour mansion in Buckinghamshire for a string of goodbye parties.

entries.title: Brisbane woman's body found in Nambour bush after ex-boyfriend arrested
entries.description: The 'loving' family of an allegedly murdered woman called police at about 7pm on Saturday after their daughter, 18, failed to return home after meeting with her ex-boyfriend, 19, at 4.30pm.

entries.title: FBI responds to 'barricade situation' inside Army base
entries.description: The FBI's National Capital Response Squad out of Washington DC is responding to a 'barricade situation' inside the United States Army base at Fort Belvoir

entries.title: An Su-30 jet crashes into houses in Siberia after pilots 'suffocate in cockpit'
entries.description: An Su-30 Russian warplane crashed into a private two-storey building in Irkutsk on Sunday and there were no casualties on the ground.

entries.title: Budget 2022: What's in the Budget for you from cheap childcare to possible scrapping of tax cuts
entries.description: Labor has promised 'responsible' measures to help Australians cope with the worst inflation in 32 years. The Budget will see new spending on childcare and subsidised medicine but no 'cash handouts'.

entries.title: Gold's Gym owner Rainer Schaller WAS on board twin-engine turboprop with his family
entries.description: Costa Rican authorities confirmed on Sunday that Gold's Gym owner Rainer Schaller, 53, his girlfriend Christiane Schikorsky, 44, and their children were on a plane that crashed off the Costa Rica coast.

entries.title: Doctor Who star Jodie Whittaker makes time to sign magazines for homeless seller
entries.description: Jodie Whittaker appears to be injecting the Time Lord's kindness into her own life as she was spotted signing copies of The Big Issue. The actress features on the cover for last week's edition.

entries.title: Red tape at green agency means clean-up workers 'banned' from doing basic tasks, source claims
entries.description: Environment Agency workers have been 'banned' from doing basic tasks such as removing blockages from rivers for months because of overzealous rules, a whistleblower has said.

entries.title: Seacliff surf ski paddler lucky to be alive after Great White shark attacks vessel
entries.description: Nat Drummond, 19, was competing in a race with Seacfliff Surf Lifesaving Club, south of Adelaide, when he was thrown into the water at 11.30am on Sunday.

entries.title: Seattle Dem who pushed police defunding fumes at cops for not investigating human feces on her lawn
entries.description: Socialist Kshama Sawant, 49, is livid at police for not addressing reports of feces being tossed in her yard after she pushed for police defunding.

entries.title: Indiana jail deputy collapses, taken to hospital after encountering fentanyl on suspect
entries.description: Deputy Brandon Creech (left), who works for the Wayne County Sherriff's Department in Richmond, Indiana, was saved by a Narcan machine inside the jail before being rushed to Reid Health Hospital.

entries.title: Sex abuse claims hit Army college for teenage recruits
entries.description: The Army Foundation College (AFC) at Harrogate is where Britain's youngest soldiers - who are too young to be sent to the front line - are introduced to military life.

entries.title: Pelosi says Dems' fight 'is not about inflation' while Bernie shares 'concern' about voter turnout
entries.description: Voters consistently rate the economy as one of their top issues going into the race. It's also become a political cudgel for Republicans who are tying rivals to Biden's handling of the economy.

entries.title: Chef snared for murder after questions from infamous 1910 Crippen trial were mimicked in court
entries.description: Ilona Golabek, 27, was hit seven times with a hammer and her body was chopped up and dumped by Kamil Ranoszek, 42, after he discovered she'd been chatting to a man on Tinder.

entries.title: Hundreds of convicted criminals including sex offenders working for police forces across the UK
entries.description: There are 284 police workers across England and Wales with convictions for crimes including corruption, sex offences, violent assaults and possession of child pornography.

entries.title: It's election DAY not election month: GOP gov candidate Kari Lake says she wants to nix early voting
entries.description: Kari Lake said that she would push to change Arizona's early voting laws if she were voted governor in the midterms, suggesting elections should be contained to one day.

entries.title: Doctor who touched patient's breast and put his hand down her trousers is struck off
entries.description: Dr Amirul Haque, who has practised in Birmingham, Dudley and Stockton-on-Tees, was struck off the register after a 'sexually motivated examination' of multiple patients, a tribunal has heard.

entries.title: Mother shocked after finding a South African tarantula the 'size of her hand' in front of her house
entries.description: Sarah Rodmell, 30, (pictured with family) was alerted to the massive spider when builders were carrying out renovations on her home in Stapleford, Nottinghamshire.

entries.title: Chip shop owner sells business after caught celebrating the Queen's death by popping champagne
entries.description: Jacki Pickett, owner of Jacki Fish and Chip Shop, in Muir of Ord, Scotland, sparked an angry mob after she shared a video of her popping and spraying champagne after Her Majesty's passing.

entries.title: Dragon's Den star, 36, found dead just one year after he won £50,000 investment for his candle firm
entries.description: Drew Cockton, who had quit his high-pressured corporate job to focus on his candle-making enterprise, impressed the Dragons with his honesty about his mental health battles.

entries.title: Yuendumu elder Ned Jampijinpa Hargraves blasts Jacinta Price over claims about Indigenous violence
entries.description: Respected Aboriginal elder  Ned Jampijinpa Hargraves in the remote outback NT community of Yuendumu has hit back at claims made by outspoken indigenous Senator Jacinta Price.

entries.title: Met Police hunt knifeman after woman in her 50s found stabbed to death as murder inquiry launched
entries.description: Police are hunting for a knifeman after a woman in her 50s was found dead at her home in Newham, east London - alongside a second woman with knife wounds, as officers launched a murder probe.

entries.title: Virginia high school has nearly 1,000 students out sick with 'flu-like symptoms'
entries.description: Stafford Senior High School in Fredericksburg, which is home to 2,000 students has nearly half of its student body out sick with 'flu-like symptoms.'

entries.title: Trump 'isn't man enough' to testify before January 6 panel Nancy Pelosi taunts
entries.description: Nancy Pelosi appeared to make an attempt at provoking Donald Trump to appear before the January 6 panel by claiming he 'isn't man enough' to comply with the subpoena for testimony.

entries.title: Dancing on Ice star Lady Leshurr charged on suspicion of assault after early hours 'screaming match'
entries.description: Lady Leshurr, 34, has been charged with two counts of actual bodily harm and will appear in custody at Thames Magistrates' Court tomorrow.

entries.title: Man, 35, is charged with the murder of 'lovely' 45-year-old mother found dead at her home
entries.description: Daniel White, 35, was charged with the murder of Angie White, 45, who was discovered in her home in Plasmarl, Swansea, in the early hours of the morning - leaving her family 'devastated'.

entries.title: Ex-NYPD Commissioner slams Adams for crime and says it is 'too dangerous to travel on the subway'
entries.description: Former NYPD Commissioner Ray Kelly, who served from 1992 to 1994 and again from 2002 to 2013, blasted Mayor Eric Adams for his soft approach to crime in New York City on Sunday.

entries.title: Just Stop Oil protestors block traffic on famous Abbey Road crossing in same pose as The Beatles
entries.description: Members of the eco-mob walked onto the pedestrian crossing in north west London at 1pm today as they continue to cause chaos on the roads of the capital.

entries.title: Air ambulance called to Theme Park after man suffers 'serious' medical emergency on rollercoaster
entries.description: A man was rushed to hospital after a 'serious' medical emergency on a theme park rollercoaster in Pembrokeshire, south west Wales, this afternoon.

entries.title: ITV vet Scott Miller confronts woman in road rage row after she 'honked horn at him for a minute'
entries.description: EXCLUSIVE: Scott Miller was called out online by David Kenward who shared dash-cam footage of the altercation and accused the vet of 'vandalising' his mother's car, which the vet denies.

entries.title: Mom finds carcinogens in the dust, soil of New Jersey high school with brain cancer cluster
entries.description: A New Jersey mom claims that she has found high levels of carcinogens in dust and soil samples taken from Colonia High School which has seen a cluster of brain tumor diagnoses in the past.

entries.title: Channel 4 faces backlash after transgender comedian stripped NAKED live on air
entries.description: The move - now being labelled as 'misogynistic', 'offensive' and spurring complaints to Ofcom - was streamed live on Channel 4's revival of Friday Night Live.

entries.title: Biden says he's physically and mentally 'functioning well' but admits age is a 'legitimate' concern
entries.description: During an interview on MSNBC's The Sunday Show, Biden was confident in his own capacities but conceded that he understood his nearing 80 was a 'concern' for some voters.

entries.title: Australia weather: NSW, Victoria and Queensland brace for floods, rain and thunderstorms
entries.description: Severe thunderstorms across much of NSW, southern Queensland and northern Victoria will bring heavy rainfall until Tuesday, which will result in floods, damaging winds and possible large hail.

entries.title: Boris Johnson gets more Cabinet backers as James Cleverly and Nadhim Zahawi support 'Boris 2.0' bid
entries.description: The former premier, who is attempting to garner enough support among Tory MPs for a return to No10, was backed by James Cleverly and Nadhim Zahawi.

entries.title: Salman Rushdie lost sight in one eye and the use of a hand in 'brutal' knife attack in New York
entries.description: Salman Rushdie, 75, was stabbed multiple times in the neck and chest as he took to the stage to give a talk on artistic freedom at the Chautauqua Institute on August 12.

entries.title: Mark McGowan begs Gina Rinehart to reconsider tearing up $15million netball sponsorship deal
entries.description: Western Australian Premier Mark McGowan wants a 'reconciliation' between Netball Australia and Gina Rinehart over the bungled $15million sponsorship deal.

entries.title: Michigan couple and their teenage sons who mysteriously vanished are spotted at gas station
entries.description: Anthony and Suzette Cirigliano, both 51, and their two sons Brandon, 19, and Noah, 15, were spotted on Monday after disappearing from their Fremont home,

entries.title: Horror as 15-year-old boy collapses and dies at Liverpool restaurant
entries.description: A 15-year-old boy collapsed and died at the popular Browns restaurant in Liverpool city centre. Members of the public and staff tended to him, but he sadly died after being rushed to hospital.

entries.title: Homeless dogs of Ukraine left on the streets because of Putin's invasion patiently line up for food
entries.description: The dogs can be seen politely waiting their turn to eat, remembering their manners in spite of their ordeal on the frontline.

entries.title: Keir Starmer calls on Tory rebels to put 'country before party' and support a GENERAL ELECTION
entries.description: In a swipe at a 'ridiculous, chaotic circus' as the Conservatives  choose a new leader for the second time this year, Sir Keir Starmer claimed voters were 'fed up to the back teeth'.

entries.title: Penny Mordaunt 'rejects' Boris Johnson's 'attempts to get her to drop out of Tory leadership race'
entries.description: The Leader of the House of Commons, who also stood to be Prime Minister in this summer's contest, is trailing both Mr Johnson and Mr Sunak in the number of publicly-declared backers.

entries.title: Biden says he 'admires the hell out of' Liz Cheney while tearing into 'mega MAGA Republicans'
entries.description: 'Look, there's nothing automatic about democracy,' President Joe Biden said during an MSNBC interview that aired on Sunday morning.

entries.title: Horrifying moment skydiver crashes to earth and dies during high school pre-game show in Tennessee
entries.description: Richard Sheffield, 55, from Elizabethton, Tennessee, was killed on Friday night in a skydiving accident while entertaining the crowds before the Musket Bowl high school football game.

entries.title: NYU professor fired after students said class was too hard urges 'tough love' from college
entries.description: Former organic chemistry professor at NYU, Maitland Jones Jr, 84, was fired in August after a group of students signed a petition against him suggesting his course was too difficult.

entries.title: Education Secretary Miguel Cardona insists Biden's student loan relief will NOT be stopped by GOP
entries.description: Joe Biden's Education Secretary Miguel Cardona insists the GOP efforts to block student loan relief will not prevail and claims they are moving forward 'full speed ahead' with implementation.

entries.title: Popular Reddit thread reveals the 75 things ANNOYING people say
entries.description: Redditors exposed the most annoying sayings and sentences they have ever heard in a viral thread on Saturday while answering the question, 'Which sentence is only used by annoying people?'

entries.title: Republicans think Ron DeSantis should have more influence than Trump over the future of the GOP
entries.description: Most voters say that if a candidate pushed Trump's claims the 2020 election was stolen, they are less likely to cast their ballot for them, a new ABC News/ Ipsos poll reveals.

entries.title: Runaway wallaby spotted in village near Newcastle for the second time in days
entries.description: A runaway wallaby has been spotted for the second time in a village near Newcastle - as the mystery remains over where it has come from.

entries.title: Stomach-churning video shows MAGGOTS squirming on ketchup dispenser at McDonald's
entries.description: A mother taking her kids to McDonald's made a gruesome discovery after finding 'maggots' squirming inside a ketchup dispenser at a branch in Letchworth, Hertfordshire.

entries.title: AOC praises UK political system on Liz Truss ouster, complains US didn't have 'take backs' for Trump
entries.description: It's not clear what political freedoms in the UK she was eyeing when contrasting the two systems. Truss' tenure came and went without a single everyday Briton casting a vote.

entries.title: Gunman who 'shot dead two maternity ward nurses at Dallas hospital' is ex-con who was out on parole
entries.description: Police said they detained Nestor Hernandez, 30, after a Methodist Health System police officer shot and wounded him at Methodist Dallas Medical Center.

entries.title: Man, 25, is charged with racist attack on Morris 'Mo' Pleasure at nightclub in Wales
entries.description: Reveller Hefin Parker, 25, (not pictured) has been charged with racially aggravated common assault and assault by beating of Earth, Wind and Fire star Morris 'Mo' Pleasure (pictured).

entries.title: Trump calls for writers of leaked Supreme Court draft overturning Roe v Wade to be put in JAIL
entries.description: Donald Trump on Saturday night told a rally in Texas that the authors of the May 5 Politico scoop should be imprisoned on 'national security' grounds if they refuse to reveal the source of their story.

entries.title: Judge in deadly Wisconsin parade trial says she's frightened by Darrell Brooks' actions in court
entries.description: Darrell Brooks, 40, allegedly plowed through the crowd at a Christmas parade in Wisconsin on November 21, 2021, killing six people between the ages of eight and 81, and injuring more than 60.

entries.title: New series of Netflix's The Crown is 'vicious' and 'would have destroyed' the Queen, friend says
entries.description: Among the most controversial scenes are reenactments of Princess Diana's funeral and the fire which tore through Windsor Castle in 1992.

entries.title: Video shows grinning Maryland governor hopeful Dan Cox accepting gift from Proud Boys
entries.description: Republican Dan Cox hopeful has denied any affiliation with the group and said he 'did not even keep the comb.'

entries.title: Riding a wave of support, Rishi? Ex-Chancellor's swimming pool complex is almost complete
entries.description: The former Chancellor of the Exchequer, who is facing competition from Boris Johnson and Penny Mordaunt for the top job, has spent £400,000 on the new pool at his North Yorkshire manor house.

entries.title: Two women savagely mauled by dog which escaped from house in Manchester
entries.description: Armed police went to Shakespeare Road,  Oldham, after the two victims were attacked by the crazed hound at 10am on Saturday. Both women were rushed to hospital with injuries.

entries.title: Major explosion kills three at gunpowder factory in Russia
entries.description: Perm Gunpowder Plant, which produces Grad and Smerch rocket launch systems for Russian troops, was set ablaze by the strikes. Two of the three people killed were reportedly burned alive.

entries.title: Shocking moment car thief rolled stolen Range Rover killing the owner's beloved Doberman
entries.description: Nicholas Oakland, 30, was found guilty of dangerous driving, aggravated vehicle taking, disqualified driving, causing unnecessary suffering to a protected animal and driving with no insurance.

entries.title: Jamie Oliver applies to convert barn into kitchen film set in the back garden of his Essex mansion
entries.description: Jamie Oliver, 47, has applied to make a film and TV studio at his £6millon country mansion in Essex. The TV chef wants to convert a barn at his family home in Finchingfield into a kitchen film set.

entries.title: NSW Police renew appeal to find Granville man Zachary Ritz
entries.description: This week is one year since western Sydney man Zachary Ritz, 45, was last seen at his unit in Inkerman Street, Granville on October 27, 2021, before he mysteriously vanished.

entries.title: American Airlines exec vows to END first class on its flights - because 'customers aren't buying'
entries.description: Chief commercial officer Vasu Raja said that the evolution of business class on flights has now made it so that there's little difference and little reason for customers to buy into the first class experience.

entries.title: Australia property prices: Reserve Bank modelling shows 20 per cent fall in national house prices
entries.description: The latest modelling from the Reserve Bank of Australia suggests the property market could crash 20 per cent below its peak within two years.

entries.title: Netball legend loses it Gina Rinehart terminated $15million sponsorship deal racism scandal
entries.description: Australian netball legend Natalie Medhurst ripped into tNetball Australia  for betraying their players over the controversial and failed $15 million sponsorship by Gina Rinehart's company.

entries.title: Police step up patrols in Leicester amid fears of clashes between Muslims and Hindus
entries.description: Police have stepped up patrols ahead of Sunday's cricket match between India and Pakistan after previous matches saw an outbreak of sectarian violence and 66 arrests.

entries.title: Nambour murder victim's ex-boyfriend is charged
entries.description: A teenager has been charged with the alleged murder with his former partner, 18, whose body was dumped in Nambour on Queensland's Sunshine Coast hours after they met in Strathpine.

entries.title: Anthony Albanese and Jodie Haydon shine at Telethon Ball
entries.description: The prime minister took a break out of his busy schedule to attend the Telethon Ball on Saturday night.

entries.title: Misrach Ewunetie's cause of death could take WEEKS to determine, official says
entries.description: Misrach Ewunetie, 20, of Euclid, Ohio, was found dead on Princeton's campus on Thursday near the tennis courts.

entries.title: Australian man sparks fiery debate after calling out a flash new housing commission building
entries.description: An Aussie bloke has gone viral with a video on social media complaining about how nice looking housing commission flats in his area were. He also commented that they have cars.

entries.title: Paid parental leave changes: Couples on $350k a year to get access
entries.description: The Albanese Government has released details of its 'family-friendly' budget, including extending paid parental leave scheme from 20 to 26 weeks and assessing the cover on a dual income basis.

entries.title: Boris allies claim Partygate probe 'does not contain any bombshells that could torpedo him'
entries.description: The ongoing Parliamentary investigation into the Partygate scandal could see Boris Johnson indicted and perhaps even expelled from Parliament.

entries.title: Jeremy Hunt's Halloween Budget will go ahead 'whoever is Prime Minister', sources suggest
entries.description: The Halloween Budget statement will go ahead regardless of who becomes Prime Minister, it was suggested last night.

entries.title: Boris Johnson wants 'loyalty' if he gives Rishi Sunak a top job, ally says amid leadership battle
entries.description: Boris Johnson is arguing that if he were to re-enter No 10 with his former Chancellor in a senior role, it would avoid a divisive battle, sources told this newspaper.

entries.title: Nearly HALF of Britons are baffled by common recycling symbols used on product packaging
entries.description: The survey of 1,097 Which? members found they made common mistakes when recycling, despite 94 per cent of respondents being 'confident' they disposed of waste correctly.

entries.title: Tony Blair's non-profit institute received funds from Russian billionaire, according to documents
entries.description: The latest accounts for former Prime Minister Tony Blair's non-profit institute reveal its links with industrial mogul Moshe Kantor (pictured left, with Vladimir Putin) who was born in Russia.

entries.title: 'No royals' to move into Windsor Castle or Buckingham during five-year renovation
entries.description: The monarch will reportedly not live in Buckingham Palace for up to five years and will instead wait for the completion of the site's £370m renovation in 2027.

entries.title: Blood donors are urged to book ahead by NHS bosses to stave off prolonged winter crisis
entries.description: Blood donors frustrated they cannot get an early appointment are being urged to book ahead amid NHS Blood and Transplant issuing a four-week-long 'amber alert' over low blood stocks.

entries.title: Texas Department of Public Safety FIRES officer who responded to Uvalde school shooting
entries.description: Sergeant Juan Maldonado was fired from the state police on Friday. He is the first state officer to be fired. The Department did not give exact reasoning for the termination.

entries.title: Haven't they grown! Trees that graced Prince William and Kate's wedding now tower over their estate
entries.description: When Prince William married Kate, Westminster Abbey was adorned with four tons of foliage, ordered by the couple to bring the flavour of a rural wedding to the imposing Central London venue.

entries.title: Gina Rinehart slams Netball Australia in scathing takedown after $15million sponsorship scrapped
entries.description: Her mining company Hancock Prospecting issued the scathing takedown as it announced it would be withdrawing its $15million sponsorship deal.

entries.title: Yours for £55: A candle that smells of Acton Lock 'with bursts of moss amber and vetiver'
entries.description: Haeckels, a Margate-based skincare and candle company, sells one called 'Acton's Lock' for £55, named after the graffiti-strewn lock on Regent's Canal, London.

entries.title: Survey estimates UK consumers hold almost £19 in unspent loyalty points per adult on average
entries.description: A new survey estimates that consumers in the UK hold about £1 billion in loyalty card points - almost £19 for each adult on average.

entries.title: Red Bull F1 team owner Dietrich Mateschitz dies after long battle with illness
entries.description: The Austrian billionaire, integral in Red Bull's involvement in F1, had been battling a long-term illness. His death was announced to Red Bull staff ahead of qualifying for Sunday's US Grand Prix in Austin.

entries.title: NHS reveals tighter rules on child transgender treatments - putting medical doctors in charge
entries.description: NHS plans for tighter rules on transgender treatments for children have been welcomed by campaigners - but criticised by trans-rights pressure groups.

entries.title: DOMINIC SANDBROOK: Why ARE we a much more Left-wing nation despite 12 years of Tory governments?
entries.description: DOMINIC SANDBROOK: Considering that the Tories have been in office, one way or another, since May 2010 - almost 12½ years - you might expect most areas of life in Britain to be markedly conservative.

entries.title: Dumped, the loyal manager who steered Mercury Prize winning British rap star Little Simz to glory
entries.description: The British rap star dumped her manager of seven years, Rob Swerdlow, just weeks before she won this year's Mercury Prize and London's Hammersmith Apollo.

entries.title: Britain faces risk of RABIES outbreak from dogs trafficked in on fake paperwork, experts warn
entries.description: Britain is at risk of a rabies outbreak from dogs trafficked into the country on fake paperwork, experts have warned (stock image).

entries.title: Shadow of Mykonos police assault hangs over England's Harry Maguire as World Cup looms
entries.description: Harry Maguire was found guilty of assaulting six police officers while on holiday in Mykonos, Greece in August 2020. He was handed a 21 month suspended prison sentence.

entries.title: Rental shortage at crisis point as 100 people line  up for two-bedroom Clovelly unit
entries.description: The frustrating reality of finding an affordable place to rent has been laid bare by video showing a line of around 100 people waiting patiently to inspect a $700 per week two-bedroom apartment in Sydney.
